p: “Don’t know” responses were coded as missing; they represent between 1.1% and 2.4% of responses for each measure and 5.8% total across all 6 measures. “Don’t know” values are left missing and not imputed. Values for other missing data were imputed. They account for between 1.3 to 1.8 % of each response for a total of 7.1% across all six measures.
